      • createTransmitter

        @Nullable
@Nullable WirelessTransmitter createTransmitter(@NotNull
                                                           @NotNull org.bukkit.Location location,
                                                           @NotNull
                                                           @NotNull UUID owner,
                                                           @NotNull
                                                           @NotNull org.bukkit.Material itemMaterial)
        Creates a new transmitter

        Note: This method will not place a block, callers must ensure that a block already exists at the given location

        Parameters:
        location - the location of the transmitter
        owner - the location of the transmitter
        itemMaterial - the material of this transmitter's item
        Returns:
        the created receiver or null if one of the following is true:
        1. location is null
        2. location's world is null
        3. the block at the location is air
        4. a component already exists at the location
